collections.name: The Matt Dobbins Collection
collections.description: Matt Dobbins is a versatile artist whose photography, digital art, and poetry capture the essence of nature, human experience, and modern life. His photography reflects a deep appreciation for landscapes and wildlife, drawing attention to the beauty in small details and grand vistas alike. His digital art explores various styles, from comic strip design to thought-provoking reflections on contemporary events. Through poetry, he delves into themes of love, loss, and personal growth, using language to connect with readers on a profound level. Across all mediums, his work invites reflection, emotion, and a deeper appreciation for the world.

collections.name: ETHEREAL AQUA
collections.description: 'Ethereal Aqua' is a collection of 12 abstract and kinetic works that reflect the intensity and depth of human emotions, utilizing constantly changing colors and movements that flow like water. Each piece is visually presented without revealing the specific emotion it represents, inviting viewers to explore and interpret according to their own feelings and experiences. This approach not only highlights the fluidity and adaptability of our emotions but also emphasizes how, like water, they are fluid, deep, and powerful, capable of transforming in unexpected ways. The series invites a deep immersion into a visual experience that is both personal and universal, reflecting the universality and uniqueness of human emotions.

collections.name: AIRHORSEONE
collections.description:
More than 50 million years ago, the ancestors of horses lived in the forested regions of North America.
The year is 2050, and horses live freely.
Some horses have moved the center of their lives from the prairie to the city.
The community of horses that have moved their center of life to the city creates an extraordinary drama.

In February 2025, 520 horses begin their quest for freedom for the first time.
